Source: https://www.coursera.org/learn/machine-learning/home/info

Machine learning
-Grew out of work in AI
-New capability for computers

Examples:
-Database mining
  Large datasets from growth of automation/web.
  E.g., Web click data, medical records, biology, engineering.
  -Applications that cannot be programmed by hand.
  E.g., Autonomous helicopter, handwriting recognition, most of Natural Language Processing(NLP),
        Computer Vision.
  -Self-customizing programs
  E.g., Amazon, Netflix product recommendations.
  -Understanding human learning (brain, real AI).
  
Machine learning definition
Arthur Samuel:
Machine learning: Field of study that gives computers the ability to learn without being
explicitly programmed.
(하나하나 프로그래밍을 하지 않아도 배울 수 있는 능력을 컴퓨터에게 주는 방법에 대한 분야.)
Tom Mitchell:
Well-posed learning problem: A computer program is said to learn from experience E with respect
to some task T and some performance measure P, if its performance on T, as measured by P,
improves with experience E.
(좋은 러닝 문제: 컴퓨터 프로그램은 어떤 태스크 T와 결과 평가 기준인 P에 대한 경험 E가 있다고 할 때,
P로 평가된 T에 대한 성능이 경험 E로부터 개선되었을 때 배웠다고 할 수 있다.)
  
Machine learning algorithms:
-Supervised learning(지도 학습)
-Unsupervised learning(비지도 학습)

Supervised learning
"Right answers" given.
For regression and classification problem.
Regression problem:
Predict results within a continuous output;
we are trying to map input variables to some continuous function.
Classification problem:
Predict results in a discrete output;
we are trying to map input variables into discrete categories.
Regression과 Classification은 예측을 한다는 점에선 동일한데 결과가 속하는 카테고리가
연속적인지 비연속적인지에 따라 나뉨. 연속적인 건 가격대나 나이 같은 게 있고 비연속적인 건 병의 유무 같은 것.

Learning algorithm deals with infinite number of features (or attributes).
-> How?
